# 🔐 Automated Log Monitoring for Failed Login Detection

## 📌 Overview
This project implements an automated log monitoring workflow to detect repeated failed login attempts, a common indicator of brute-force attacks.

The solution improves visibility into authentication activity and provides a repeatable method for identifying suspicious patterns in system logs.

---

## ⚙️ Approach

- Processed authentication logs (`/var/log/auth.log`) using Bash  
- Extracted failed login attempts using `grep`  
- Aggregated attempts by IP using `awk`, `sort`, and `uniq`  
- Applied a threshold (>5 attempts) to flag suspicious activity  
- Used Python to validate results and generate structured output  
- Automated execution using cron  

---

## 📊 Key Results

- Analyzed multiple log samples to detect failed login patterns  
- No activity exceeded defined thresholds during testing  
